Detailed Description

Small interface for functions that know how to make an instance of themselves given a map of key, value parameters.

Idea is that you can call this class's static methods generically and cast appropriately.

static SelfCreate* SelfCreate::newObject ( std::map< std::string, std::string > &  param  )  [inline, static]

This static function should be overridden by child classes to return an object of the correct type initialized correctly with the parameters in the string, string map.

All objects created this way should be deleted when finished using.

Parameters:
param - Map of key/value pairs to initialize the object.
Returns:
Pointer toCreate object, this should be sub casted as necessary.

Create an object requested by the specification string by matching it against the self documenting classes and then calling the matching self creator function.

Resulting object must be delete'd when done.

Parameters:
spec - String specification of object requested.
docs - Vector of selfdoc objects to look in for name of object to be made.
creators - Vector of creation functions to use for creating object.
typeDescription - What type of object are we attempting to make?
error - If true call errAbort when don't recognize value, otherwise return NULL.
Returns:
Pointer to new SelfCreate object, delete when finished.
